WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.000
We invited the top 20 engine manufacturers for diesels.

00:06.000 --> 00:09.000
Rolls Royce, Cummins, Cat, Detroit Diesel.

00:09.000 --> 00:10.000
All of them showed up.

00:10.000 --> 00:13.000
We got them all to sign in on our sign in book.

00:13.000 --> 00:21.000
And then we fired up a 480 horsepower diesel engine on junk.

00:21.000 --> 00:26.000
Pickle juice, Mountain Dew, coffee, soda pop, anything we could throw in the fuel tank.

00:26.000 --> 00:28.000
Fired it up, no pollution.

00:28.000 --> 00:35.120
Well, the big corporations didn't send CEOs and presidents that make decisions. They sent their engineers out

00:37.000 --> 00:40.640
Now on film with hidden cameras in the room

00:41.720 --> 00:46.280
We turn the main camera off and we said now. What do you think of this? Well, we don't understand it

00:47.200 --> 00:50.940
Well, are you going to go back and tell your bosses what you saw? No

00:50.940 --> 00:55.780
No. Why not? Well, we go back and tell them we see zero pollution after we just spent

00:55.780 --> 01:03.380
$50 million to get 1% or 2% improvement, and we look like dummies. So we're going to go

01:03.380 --> 01:07.240
back and tell them this shit doesn't work. You were talking about putting this thing

01:07.240 --> 01:12.000
on a diesel for a monster truck, right? Well, we've had them on trucks. I sold one diesel

01:12.000 --> 01:18.520
Peterbilt I had here, or Freightliner. I sold that for $65,000. Now, is the size of the

01:18.520 --> 01:22.940
tube and the gate, is that almost like the displacement of a cylinder normally, kind of?

01:22.940 --> 01:27.240
Well, you're comparing it to an engine again. Sort of, kind of. It makes fuel for anything

01:27.240 --> 01:32.980
that uses fuel. I can fire up a little three horsepower engine and make enough fuel from

01:32.980 --> 01:40.680
that engine to power a city. Yeah, because now it produces hydrogen, right? It's a hydrogen-like

01:40.680 --> 01:48.160
substance and weight, but it does not explode, it implodes. Oh, okay, okay. So once you have

01:48.160 --> 01:53.600
perfect burn going no pollution coming out the tailpipe and in most cases actually more oxygen

01:53.600 --> 01:59.280
coming out the tailpipe than there is in the air at that point you're making so much energy

01:59.280 --> 02:06.640
you don't need it all yeah we have more energy coming off the exhaust pipe than you get off the

02:06.640 --> 02:15.040
shaft of the engine yeah so we're doing uh when william shatner called up and we chatted with him

02:15.040 --> 02:20.480
he said it sounded like star trek technology and i laughed i said well if you remember the first

02:20.480 --> 02:27.680
few episodes where they sent scotty up the tube up the plasma reactor to fix the plasma reactor

02:27.680 --> 02:33.200
you saw this big glass crystal tube with a pipe inside it and a rod inside it

02:34.160 --> 02:38.240
the shape of the rod wasn't right but everything else was right and when they were showing the

02:38.240 --> 02:43.920
lightning bolts going through it that's exactly what's happening in the geek so he starts laughing

02:43.920 --> 02:49.000
and go, you need to tell me this is another invention that we first got to show on Star

02:49.000 --> 02:50.000
Trek?

02:50.000 --> 02:51.300
I'm writing a book about this.

